00:53:40,242 --> 00:53:43,828
What the hell are you looking at?

470
00:53:51,960 --> 00:53:53,711
- That's all right.
- No way.

471
00:53:53,962 --> 00:53:57,172
No, really. It's good.
Look, I'm not kidding.

472
00:53:57,422 --> 00:54:02,051
- Are you serious?
- I'm serious. It's good!

473
00:54:03,886 --> 00:54:06,263
- You gotta try that!
- That's good!

474
00:54:06,513 --> 00:54:08,682
That's great!

475
00:54:08,931 --> 00:54:12,101
Katie?

476
00:54:17,730 --> 00:54:21,275
Katie?

477
00:54:40,039 --> 00:54:42,208
Can I tell you something else?
We get back...

478
00:54:42,458 --> 00:54:48,045
...I'm gonna take my money
and I'm gonna buy you a bathtub.

479
00:54:48,296 --> 00:54:52,507
I'll get you a lifetime supply
of titty magazines and toilet paper!

480
00:54:52,757 --> 00:54:56,803
I already beat you to it, bro!

481
00:55:00,598 --> 00:55:03,766
There's something on your...

482
00:55:21,280 --> 00:55:24,742
Katie?

483
00:58:27,929 --> 00:58:31,306
Who, me?

484
00:58:35,267 --> 00:58:39,145
Francesca, I know
all of this isn't real.

485
00:58:39,395 --> 00:58:44,024
So I'm just gonna go with it, okay?

486
00:58:45,609 --> 00:58:50,488
Can't cheat on your fiancée
with a dead girl, right?

487
00:59:16,842 --> 00:59:20,762
Her parents.

488
00:59:22,012 --> 00:59:25,432
Please.

489
00:59:25,891 --> 00:59:29,811
Don't close it.

490
00:59:31,562 --> 00:59:35,399
Haven't seen them for years.

491
00:59:35,649 --> 00:59:38,317
They moved to New York.

492
00:59:38,568 --> 00:59:42,863
I was on my way to join them.

493
00:59:43,155 --> 00:59:46,115
But they're dead now.

494
00:59:46,866 --> 00:59:49,493
- How would you know?
- When you're like this...

495
00:59:49,743 --> 00:59:53,121
...you know these things.

496
00:59:53,454 --> 00:59:56,623
My mother...

497
00:59:56,707 --> 00:59:59,834
...she made me this dress.

498
01:00:00,084 --> 01:00:02,795
Do you like it?

499
01:00:06,548 --> 01:00:10,259
You remind me of her.

500
01:00:10,301 --> 01:00:14,096
I don't think so.

501
01:00:15,263 --> 01:00:20,225
Well, here. You should have this back.

502
01:00:25,396 --> 01:00:30,275
Oh, God, you really are
a fucking ghost.

503
01:00:33,569 --> 01:00:37,239
Where are you going?

504
01:00:48,998 --> 01:00:54,836
Santos was my goddamn responsibility.

505
01:01:06,304 --> 01:01:10,516
- The "Lorelei".
- She was adrift. We rescued her.

506
01:01:10,766 --> 01:01:15,478
I've heard the story of the "Lorelei".

507
01:01:15,603 --> 01:01:20,106
I didn't know the "Graza" was involved.

508
01:01:21,107 --> 01:01:25,152
The gold was onboard the "Lorelei"?

509
01:01:25,319 --> 01:01:30,990
It says here "May 19, 1962".

510
01:01:31,240 --> 01:01:36,327
That's two days before
your ship disappeared.

511
01:01:36,953 --> 01:01:42,082
There were no survivors
onboard the "Lorelei".

512
01:01:48,170 --> 01:01:51,005
Jesus Christ!

513
01:01:54,676 --> 01:01:58,303
Where you going?

514
01:02:17,068 --> 01:02:20,320
Most spirits are free
to be with their families.

515
01:02:20,571 --> 01:02:25,032
So why aren't you with yours?

516
01:02:26,868 --> 01:02:31,288
- We're all trapped here.
- Who?

517
01:02:31,538 --> 01:02:34,123
My shipmates and I.

518
01:02:34,373 --> 01:02:37,126
Even the ones who aren't marked.

519
01:02:37,376 --> 01:02:38,626
Marked?

520
01:02:38,877 --> 01:02:40,962
Katie, what do you mean?

521
01:02:41,212 --> 01:02:44,548
When the boat's full...

522
01:02:44,798 --> 01:02:47,092
What? You can tell me.

523
01:02:47,342 --> 01:02:53,764
When he has all the souls he needs
and has filled his quota...

524
01:02:54,181 --> 01:02:57,058
...we'll all be ferried...

525
01:02:57,309 --> 01:02:59,810
...to...

526
01:03:00,060 --> 01:03:03,271
What is it? What's wrong?

527
01:03:03,897 --> 01:03:07,150
- What is it?
- He doesn't want me talking to you.

528
01:03:07,399 --> 01:03:10,027
- He who?
- But I'm not like the others!

529
01:03:10,277 --> 01:03:11,862
You need to tell me.

530
01:03:12,111 --> 01:03:16,365
You must go at once.
Leave the ship while you still can!

531
01:03:16,616 --> 01:03:19,993
Katie, what is it?

532
01:03:20,202 --> 01:03:24,997
Katie! Katie?

533
01:03:25,247 --> 01:03:27,415
Epps?

534
01:03:27,665 --> 01:03:29,626
Come on!

535
01:03:29,876 --> 01:03:32,920
We have to leave.

536
01:03:34,171 --> 01:03:37,507
Where you going, Murphy?

537
01:03:39,509 --> 01:03:42,511
What's the matter? It's me.

538
01:03:42,761 --> 01:03:44,429
Santos.

539
01:03:44,679 --> 01:03:49,683
It's no fun lying
at the bottom of the ocean.

540
01:03:51,768 --> 01:03:56,522
No lights at the end of the tunnel.
Not for me, Murph.

541
01:03:56,772 --> 01:04:01,109
No 10,000 virgins at the pearly gates.

542
01:04:02,443 --> 01:04:06,279
Because of the plan, I'm trapped
on this dreamboat of yours.

543
01:04:06,530 --> 01:04:12,493
So you know what?
You're coming along for the ride.

544
01:04:33,343 --> 01:04:36,512
No!

545
01:04:43,351 --> 01:04:45,978
Murphy?

546
01:04:55,819 --> 01:04:59,572
You all right, Murph?

547
01:05:00,322 --> 01:05:03,199
You okay?

548
01:05:05,827 --> 01:05:09,580
- What's the matter, Murph?
- It's me!

549
01:05:15,168 --> 01:05:20,714
- It's me!
- Do it, come on. It'll make you feel good.

550
01:05:26,677 --> 01:05:29,220
Come on!

551
01:05:34,767 --> 01:05:38,519
- Come on!
- Hey!

552
01:05:44,649 --> 01:05:49,236
Oh, God.
Epps, you okay?

553
01:05:52,238 --> 01:05:55,783
- Keep him in the aquarium.
- No, listen. He was drunk.

554
01:05:56,033 --> 01:05:58,827
He didn't know what he was doing.

555
01:05:59,078 --> 01:06:03,664
Look, he just tried to kill you.
He stays in there.

556
01:06:03,915 --> 01:06:07,959
Let's go find Greer.

557
01:06:17,592 --> 01:06:19,802
Any sign of him?

558
01:06:20,052 --> 01:06:21,470
No, we looked all over.

559
01:06:21,720 --> 01:06:25,264
Man's pissed off.
Seems to happen on this boat.

560
01:06:25,515 --> 01:06:28,851
- Least we weren't around 40 years ago.
- The passengers were poisoned...

561
01:06:29,102 --> 01:06:33,271
...to get to the gold? Isn't that...?
- Extreme? Maybe, but if the shoe fits...

562
01:06:33,522 --> 01:06:36,524
Next thing you know,
we'll be trying to kill each other.

563
01:06:36,774 --> 01:06:40,693
- What's with the heart?
- Found it. Belonged to this little girl.

564
01:06:40,944 --> 01:06:44,446
- What girl?
- She told me to get off this boat.

565
01:06:44,696 --> 01:06:48,158
- She's talking to you now?
- What are you talking about?

566
01:06:48,409 --> 01:06:51,702
- You're seeing ghosts, Epps?
- Just forget it.

567
01:06:51,953 --> 01:06:53,912
So the ship's got a few kinks.

568
01:06:54,162 --> 01:06:58,165
Let's stick with Munder's specs
and try to fix the ship.

569
01:06:58,416 --> 01:07:01,669
No way five people and the gold
will fit on any raft.

570
01:07:01,919 --> 01:07:05,380
Murphy's not going anywhere,
and we're not leaving him here.

571
01:07:05,630 --> 01:07:11,218
We stick with the plan. Fix the boat.
Let's get going. Come on.

572
01:07:20,183 --> 01:07:22,852
<i>That's the collision bulkhead hatch.</i>

573
01:07:23,102 --> 01:07:26,605
<i>- Wheel's busted. It won't open.
- Arming the C4.</i>

574
01:07:26,856 --> 01:07:27,856
<i>- Dodge?
- I'm good.</i>

575
01:07:28,106 --> 01:07:29,441
<i>- Munder?
- I'm good.</i>

576
01:07:29,691 --> 01:07:33,152
<i>Contact.</i>

577
01:07:35,821 --> 01:07:39,407
<i>- There's the tear, portside.
- Looks bigger from here.</i>

578
01:07:39,657 --> 01:07:43,827
<i>- I'll shut her up.
- No problem.</i>

579
01:07:44,911 --> 01:07:50,833
<i>- Munder, rudder's fixed. You all right?
- I'm good.</i>

580
01:07:51,082 --> 01:07:55,878
<i>- What do you think, Dodge?
- She'll hold.</i>

581
01:07:57,671 --> 01:08:01,674
<i>- We're set with the pumps.
- Start them up.</i>

582
01:08:01,924 --> 01:08:04,886
Copy that, Epps.
One and two, kicking in.

583
01:08:05,136 --> 01:08:08,680
- I give it 12 hours till she's bone-dry.
- Both on full.

584
01:08:08,930 --> 01:08:11,974
<i>Get ready, Epps. Here it comes.</i>

585
01:08:12,224 --> 01:08:15,101
<i>Great work, guys.</i>

586
01:08:32,282 --> 01:08:36,619
Damn. Current's faster than I thought.

587
01:08:37,036 --> 01:08:43,291
If we control her drift, headed in this
direction, we should clear those islands.

588
01:08:43,541 --> 01:08:46,377
We'll keep it afloat
until we get picked up.

589
01:08:46,627 --> 01:08:49,796
Son of a bitch.
We may just get out of this yet.

590
01:08:50,046 --> 01:08:51,172
Kazillionaires.

591
01:08:51,422 --> 01:08:54,132
Check on the bridge
when you're done here.

592
01:08:54,383 --> 01:08:58,469
I'll see if I can find Greer
down below.

593
01:09:01,514 --> 01:09:05,141
Greer?

594
01:09:20,070 --> 01:09:23,322
Katie?

595
01:09:34,331 --> 01:09:38,167
Greer? Jesus!

596
01:09:44,297 --> 01:09:46,882
- Shit.
- Number two's clogged. Who's going?

597
01:09:47,133 --> 01:09:50,720
You go.

598
01:09:50,970 --> 01:09:54,556
Shit. Every single time!

599
01:09:56,181 --> 01:09:58,642
Oh, my God.

600
01:09:58,892 --> 01:10:02,311
Come with me.

601
01:10:02,520 --> 01:10:06,064
I want to show you something.

602
01:14:27,438 --> 01:14:28,982
No!

603
01:14:29,232 --> 01:14:31,650
Come on! No!

604
01:14:31,900 --> 01:14:35,027
Come on!

605
01:14:35,278 --> 01:14:40,115
You can't die on me!

606
01:15:32,823 --> 01:15:35,534
Dodge. Murphy's dead.

607
01:15:35,784 --> 01:15:38,119
- What?
- We have to get off this boat.

608
01:15:38,369 --> 01:15:42,456
There's a reason you, me and Munder are
still alive. That's why he came after us.

609
01:15:42,706 --> 01:15:48,210
- To fix his ship.
- I just saw Murphy. What's happening?

610
01:15:49,795 --> 01:15:52,964
I don't know.

611
01:15:53,632 --> 01:15:55,967
I want you and Dodge
on the rudder.

612
01:15:56,217 --> 01:15:58,719
- But you just said...
- Listen to me.

613
01:15:58,969 --> 01:16:04,933
I'll get Munder, we'll see if the welds
are holding. Stay here till we get back.

614
01:16:05,183 --> 01:16:09,102
I do not want you out of
each other's sight. Take this.

615
01:16:09,353 --> 01:16:12,855
Take it.

616
01:16:13,314 --> 01:16:17,776
- Be careful down there.
- I will.

617
01:17:10,985 --> 01:17:14,570
- That's it, then. We made it.
- For now.

618
01:17:14,821 --> 01:17:17,824
- I'll check on Epps.
- No, she said to wait here.

619
01:17:18,074 --> 01:17:23,077
- Yeah, but...
- Hey, she said to wait! So wait.

620
01:17:35,337 --> 01:17:36,964
You disgust me.

621
01:17:37,214 --> 01:17:39,924
- What did you say?
- You heard me.

622
01:17:40,174 --> 01:17:44,177
You're a pathetic excuse for a man.
She says, "Jump", and you jump.

623
01:17:44,428 --> 01:17:49,140
You're disgusting.
I don't have time for this.

624
01:17:53,518 --> 01:17:58,147
- Who the hell are you?
- The question is, who are you?

625
01:17:58,397 --> 01:18:01,691
You worship her, yet you've
never had the balls to tell her...

626
01:18:01,941 --> 01:18:04,944
...because you're a weak,
cowardly child.

627
01:18:05,194 --> 01:18:12,325
However, if you'll kindly step out of
my way, I'll make your dream a reality.

628
01:18:12,575 --> 01:18:17,621
You know, Dodge, if you kill somebody,
you go to hell.

629
01:18:18,455 --> 01:18:23,542
Well, you live for her.
You willing to die for her?

630
01:19:06,201 --> 01:19:09,495
I shot Ferriman. He's dead.

631
01:19:09,745 --> 01:19:12,456
Yeah? Don't be so sure, Dodge.

632
01:19:12,706 --> 01:19:16,459
- What are you doing?
- Trip's over. I'm sinking the boat.

633
01:19:16,709 --> 01:19:19,253
- It's taken its last victim.
- That'll kill us.

634
01:19:19,503 --> 01:19:22,130
- We'll have to take our chances.
- What about the gold?

635
01:19:22,381 --> 01:19:26,676
Fucking kidding? We're not getting the
gold off this boat. Nobody ever does.

636
01:19:26,926 --> 01:19:29,135
Wait, wait. Wait!

637
01:19:29,386 --> 01:19:33,055
That gold can give us everything
we ever wanted.

638
01:19:33,305 --> 01:19:36,809
We could have our own boat.
The two of us.

639
01:19:37,059 --> 01:19:40,228
We could have a life together.
You and me.

640
01:19:40,478 --> 01:19:45,148
What are you talking about?
Dodge, we gotta get out of here. Now.

641
01:19:45,399 --> 01:19:49,485
Well, I can't let you do that.

642
01:19:55,574 --> 01:19:59,034
So that's it, huh?

643
01:19:59,368 --> 01:20:01,953
All right. Okay.

644
01:20:02,203 --> 01:20:06,124
You win. All right.

645
01:20:07,457 --> 01:20:09,543
Fucking bitch!

646
01:20:09,751 --> 01:20:12,336
All right, you win! Go ahead, do it!

647
01:20:12,587 --> 01:20:14,839
Go ahead. Blow it up!

648
01:20:15,089 --> 01:20:18,008
Kill us all!

649
01:20:19,092 --> 01:20:25,306
Hey, Dodge. Why haven't you
asked me where Munder is?

650
01:20:30,934 --> 01:20:35,022
Well, I suppose that's because...

651
01:20:35,272 --> 01:20:37,231
...I already know.

652
01:20:37,481 --> 01:20:41,067
- You won't pull that trigger, Maureen.
- Try me.

653
01:20:41,318 --> 01:20:46,113
Dodge made the same mistake.
He's dead.

654
01:20:46,614 --> 01:20:48,365
Katie told you, didn't she?

655
01:20:48,616 --> 01:20:52,744
Souls without sin can't be marked.
Makes them tough to control.

656
01:20:52,994 --> 01:20:56,330
But as long as I keep the boat afloat,
we'll all go down together.

657
01:20:56,580 --> 01:20:59,957
- What the fuck are you?
- I'm a salvager.

658
01:21:00,208 --> 01:21:05,045
Just like you.
You collect ships, I collect souls.

659
01:21:05,295 --> 01:21:08,798
And when I fill my quota,
I send a boatload home.

660
01:21:09,048 --> 01:21:12,760
This will make management happy.
You see, it's a job.

661
01:21:13,010 --> 01:21:15,553
Given to me after a lifetime of sin.

662
01:21:15,803 --> 01:21:21,725
So if I lose this ship, management won't
be happy, which is not a good thing.

663
01:21:21,975 --> 01:21:26,103
I'm not getting through to you.
I'm asking for an exchange.

664
01:21:26,354 --> 01:21:28,563
This ship for your life.

665
01:21:28,813 --> 01:21:30,982
I want my crew back.

666
01:21:31,233 --> 01:21:35,402
Sorry. Once a passenger's marked,
they're mine.

667
01:21:35,653 --> 01:21:39,572
Then I guess it's over.

668
01:21:47,745 --> 01:21:51,499
All you had to do was fix the ship!

669
01:21:54,167 --> 01:21:57,003
I gave you a great opportunity.

670
01:21:57,253 --> 01:22:01,006
All you had to do was take it.

671
01:22:04,342 --> 01:22:08,679
What are you gonna do, shoot me?

672
01:25:31,006 --> 01:25:35,384
Careful. Hang in there, ma'am.

673
01:26:00,612 --> 01:26:03,472
No!

